$ Golomb Ruler 
$
$ Basic Problem Model using Quaternary constraints
$ (Smith et al 'Modelling the Golomb Ruler Problem')
$
$ by Andrea Rendl

language ESSENCE' 1.0

given n : int
letting TICKS  be domain int(1..n)

find ruler : matrix indexed by [TICKS] of int(0..n**2)

minimising ruler[n]

such that

  $ monotonicity
  forall i,j : TICKS .
     ((i< j) /\ (j <= n)) =>
      (ruler[i] < ruler[j]),

  $ distinction 
  forall i,j,k,l : TICKS .
       ((i < j) /\ (k < l) /\ ((j>l) \/ (i>k))) => 
             (ruler[j] - ruler[i] != ruler[l] - ruler[k])


